statement.p:
Solve the following system using augmented matrix methods:
\begin{array}{c}
3 x  - 6 y = -33
\\
7 x  - 14 y = -77
\end{array}

p.me:
A + B^T=\left(\begin{array}{cc} 
            a_{11} \amp  a_{12} \cr
	    a_{21} \amp  a_{22} 
	   \end{array}\right)

A - B + C^T=\left(\begin{array}{cc} 
            c_{11} \amp  c_{12} \cr
	    c_{21} \amp  c_{22}
	   \end{array}\right)

A^T B^T=\left(\begin{array}{cc} 
            c_{11} \amp  c_{12} \cr
	    c_{21} \amp  c_{22} 
	   \end{array}\right)

A^{-1}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc} 
            a_{11} \amp  a_{12} \amp  a_{13} \cr
	    a_{21} \amp  a_{22} \amp  a_{23} \cr 
	    a_{31} \amp  a_{32} \amp  a_{33}
	    \end{array}\right)

static.solution:
A{ f b}=\left[ egin{matrix} 3 \amp 5 \cr 3 \amp 2 \cr -7 \amp -4\cr \end{matrix}ight] \left[ egin{matrix} 3 \cr -4 \cr \end{matrix}ight]= \left[ egin{matrix} -11 \cr 1 \cr -5 \cr \end{matrix}ight] 
e { f 0}, so { f b}
ot\in \ker(T).
Since the range of T is a subset of {\mathbb R}^3 and { f c}\in{\mathbb R}^2, { f c}
ot\in range(T).

solution.p:
(a,b,c) is in the image of T if and only if T(x_1,x_2,x_3)=(a,b,c), 
that is, if and only if 
\begin{aligned} x_1-x_2 \amp = a \\ x_2-x_3 \amp = b \\ x_3-x_1 \amp = c \end{aligned}
The matrix 
\begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp  -1 \amp  0 \amp  a \\ 0 \amp  1 \amp  -1 \amp  b \\ -1 \amp  0 \amp  1 \amp  c \end{bmatrix}
represents this system of equations.  Row reducing, one obtains
\begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp  -1 \amp  0 \amp  a \\ 0 \amp  1 \amp  -1 \amp  b \\ 0 \amp  0 \amp  0 \amp  a+b+c \end{bmatrix}
Thus the system has a solution if and only if a+b+c = 0, that is,  (a,b,c) is in the image of T if and only if a+b+c = 0.

